Repo clone
Create an empty repo
Create a new floder , open it with VS code
Clone Command
git clone (repo_link)

Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate

Create the requirement txt file (Use at last after writing the complete code)
pip freeze > requirements.txt

Share environment set up to git hub
Cerate a .gitignore file

Example work flow 
git init                      # Start Git repo
git add .                     # Stage everything
git commit -m "Initial commit"  # Save a snapshot of staged files


Initializes a new Git repository in your current project folder
git init

Adds all files and folders in your current directory
git add .
git add .  # Adds everything in the current directory
git add file.py # Adds only file.py
git add folder/ # Adds all files inside folder/
git add -A # Adds all changes (new, modified, deleted)

The git commit command saves a snapshot of your project in its current state
git commit -m "Your message here"

Push Your Code to GitHub
git push -u origin main

